Reasoning: The paper deals with shape formation in distributed systems of programmable particles, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The problem of shape recovery after a certain number of particles have crashed involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed algorithms (cs.DS). The use of semi-synchronous adversarial scheduler suggests the involvement of control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO).
